### Health Check
GET http://localhost:8081/health

### Check Email (New User)
POST http://localhost:8081/auth/check-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newuser@example.com"
}

### Check Email (Existing User)
POST http://localhost:8081/auth/check-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### Request Verification Code
POST http://localhost:8081/auth/verify/request
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newuser@example.com"
}

### Verify Code (Invalid)
POST http://localhost:8081/auth/verify/check
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "code": "000000"
}

### Complete Registration (Must get code from logs/db first, assume mock/log for now or test failure)
# NOTE: You need to check the server logs for the generated code to make this work!
POST http://localhost:8081/auth/register/complete
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword",
  "first_name": "John",
  "last_name": "Doe",
  "code": "123456" 
}

